      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">DWS vs TLS — When to Choose Which</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200"><span class="text-white font-medium">TLS is better for one expensive tile</span> (Z on TLS = +20 bonus). <span class="text-white font-medium">DWS is better for expensive words</span> (QUARTZ on DWS = +24 bonus). Rule of thumb: if your word scores 12+ points, DWS gives more bonus than TLS on any single tile. Below 12 points, TLS on your best tile wins.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Use DWS When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Word scores 12+ base points. Multiple high-value tiles. Longer words (5-7 letters). Total word value matters more than any single tile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">→ Use TLS When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Short word (2-3 letters) with one power tile. Z, Q, X, or J is your only high scorer. Word total is under 12 points. Precise tile positioning possible.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for DWS Plays</h2>

